  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to assess whether radiographic osteoarthritis severity (OA;
      Kellgren-Lawrence scale) is associated with self-reported improvement in pain after
      non-surgical treatments (physiotherapy, pain killers, injection, other treatments).

      The hypothesis is that radiographic OA severity is inversely associated with self-reported
      improvement.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
